7. Conversion Messaging Frameworks

Functional Messaging
	•	“Support better sleep/digestion/focus/energy naturally.”
	•	“Feel the difference in as little as timeframe.”
	•	“Clinically-backed ingredients, real-life results.”

Emotional Messaging
	•	“Finally feel like yourself again.”
	•	“More calm days. More restful nights.”
	•	“Show up as your best self—every day.”

Lifestyle Messaging
	•	“Your new daily wellness ritual.”
	•	“Simple. Effective. Backed by real science.”

Objection Handling
	•	“Backed by third-party testing.”
	•	“No fillers, dyes, or artificial junk.”
	•	“Clear dosages. No proprietary blends.”

⸻

8. FAQ & Objection Handling (Supplements)

“Is it safe?”

Answer: [Explain testing, certifications, manufacturing standards]

“Will it work for me?”

Answer: [Set expectations + share average customer results]

“How long until I see results?”

Answer: [Give a real, honest timeframe: 3–7 days, 2–4 weeks, etc.]

“Does it interact with medications?”

Answer: [Standard FDA-safe disclaimer to consult a doctor]

“How is this different from other supplements?”

Answer: [Highlight purity, dosing, absorption, science]

⸻

9. Content Creation Guidelines (Supplements)
	1.	Lead with functional benefit first.
	2.	Use clear science but simplify the explanation.
	3.	Never make unapproved medical claims (FTC/FDA safe).
	4.	Focus on purity, safety, testing, and trust.
	5.	Use social proof—a MUST for supplements.
	6.	Explain why the ingredients matter.
	7.	Use rituals → habits → identity messaging.
	8.	Include before/after expectations without making medical promises.

⸻

10. Versioning & Updates

Update this document when:
	•	New clinical studies or ingredient research becomes available
	•	Dosages or formulas improve
	•	New flavors or forms launch (powder → gummies)
	•	Testing standards update (more rigorous lab tests)
	•	Customer reviews reveal new benefit angles

